---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<div>
    <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12">How to Play</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                <div>
                    <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">1</div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Rule One.</h3>
                    <p>There are 12 cards face up in a grid. There are 81 cards in total. Each card has four features: shape, color, shading, and number. </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">2</div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Rule Two</h3>
                    <p>Players look for a "set" of three cards where, for each feature (shape, color, shading, number), the cards are either all the same or all different.</p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <div class="text-6xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-4">3</div>
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Rule Three</h3>
                    <p>When you spot a set, tap on the three cards! If correct, take the cards and replace them with new ones from the deck. If no set exists, add three more cards. The game ends when the deck is empty and no more sets are possible.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>